<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Restaurant range with salamander service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Heavy-duty restaurant ranges with integrated salamander broilers. Premium niche, fewer LA shops handle.</h2>

    <p>Restaurant ranges with integrated salamander broilers are the heavy-duty premium tier of commercial cooking. $15,000 to $30,000+ install. The salamander, a high-heat finishing broiler mounted above the range top, reaches 800 to 1,200°F at the broiler grate. Restaurant chefs use the salamander for the final 30 to 60 second finish on plated dishes (cheese melt, browning, finishing steaks). Integrated salamander gives the cook line one continuous workstation; the salamander positions for the chef to slide a plate or pan directly from the range surface under the broiler without moving stations.</p>

    <p>The dominant brands: <strong>Vulcan VR-60 with salamander</strong>, <strong>Wolf Challenger XL CHSC60 with integrated salamander</strong> (Wolf Industrial / Sub-Zero Group commercial division, distinct from residential Wolf), <strong>Garland US-Range U Series with salamander</strong> (Welbilt), <strong>Montague Legend with salamander</strong>. LA installations: Beverly Hills steakhouses, Bel Air private dining, Hollywood premium restaurants, Pasadena fine dining, West Hollywood premium operations.</p>

    <p>Most LA appliance shops decline salamander work. Specialty equipment, fewer trained techs, premium tier customer base with white-glove service expectations. We service salamanders routinely; the niche fits our practitioner model. Salamander work is often combined with range component repair on the same dispatch (single-visit efficiency saves the operator a return-visit fee).</p>

    <p><strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</strong> BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410).  scope. BBB A+ accredited.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 SALAMANDER FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Salamander-specific failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Salamander failures distinct from range failures. Higher heat, faster wear.</h2>

    <ol class="failure-list">
      <li><strong>Salamander igniter (year 3 to 5).</strong> Faster wear than range burner igniters because of higher heat exposure plus more frequent ignition cycles. Replacement $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Salamander thermocouple.</strong> Same wear pattern, accelerated by heat. Often replaced as paired set with the igniter. $220 to $340.</li>
      <li><strong>Salamander burner head.</strong> Continuous 800 to 1,200°F exposure deforms the burner head over years. Gas distribution becomes uneven, broil pattern goes off. Replacement $480 to $720.</li>
      <li><strong>Salamander door / shield mechanism.</strong> Heavy door with hinge and counterweight system. Hinge wear, counterweight slip. $400 to $640 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Salamander broiler grate.</strong> Cast iron or stainless grate warps from continuous high-heat cycling, year 6 to 9. $290 to $540 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot system (older salamanders).</strong> Pre-electronic-ignition models with standing pilots. Pilot orifice clogged or thermocouple weak. $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Range component failures (separate diagnostic).</strong> Range burners, oven thermostat, range gas valve, see <a href="/commercial/range-repair/gas-range-repair/">commercial gas range repair</a> for range diagnostic context.</li>
      <li><strong>Salamander gas valve.</strong> Less common, but year 8+ valve degradation creates pressure inconsistencies. $580 to $880.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent salamander range repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Four salamander range jobs from the past 90 days. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Steakhouse in Beverly Hills · Vulcan VR-60 with salamander, 8 years old</h3>
        <p>Salamander igniter intermittent plus thermocouple weak (gas valve cycling on the salamander). Replaced salamander igniter and thermocouple as paired set per standard practice. Tested salamander 5 ignition cycles before leaving. Total: $120 + $360 igniter + $240 thermocouple = $720. Range below tested fine, no additional service required.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hollywood premium restaurant · Wolf Challenger XL CHSC60 with integrated salamander, 7 years old</h3>
        <p>Salamander burner head deformed (uneven broil pattern noticed by chef during finishing service). Diagnosed: heat-cycling deformation typical at 7 years on heavy-volume operation. Replaced salamander burner head with OEM Wolf Industrial part (different parts catalog from residential Wolf, ordered through commercial authorized network). Total: $120 + $640 burner head + $130 labor = $890.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Bel Air private dining · Garland US-Range U-72 with salamander, 9 years old</h3>
        <p>Salamander door not closing reliably (counterweight slip) plus salamander igniter at end-of-life. Replaced salamander door hinge and counterweight assembly plus igniter. Chef noted improvement in service flow on first dinner service after repair. Total: $120 + $560 door mechanism + $300 igniter = $980.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Fine dining in Pasadena · Montague Legend 60\" with salamander, 11 years old</h3>
        <p>Multi-component reactive: salamander burner head deformed plus range thermocouple weak. Combined repair in single visit. Replaced salamander burner head plus range thermocouple. Total: $120 + $720 salamander burner + $260 range thermocouple + $100 supplies = $1,200. Recommended quarterly maintenance contract going forward to catch the next failure earlier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we service, what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Vulcan VR-60 with salamander, Wolf Challenger XL CHSC60 with integrated salamander, Garland US-Range U Series with salamander, Montague Legend with salamander, and other heavy-duty restaurant ranges with integrated salamander broilers. Salamander igniter, thermocouple, burner head, broiler grate, door and shield mechanism, pilot system, gas valve. Range components on the same unit (paired diagnostic). Combined dispatch for salamander plus range work in a single visit.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>New salamander installation or new salamander/range combination installation (specialty installer trade)</li>
      <li>LA fire marshal pre-fire permit issuance (city / county jurisdiction); we document equipment for operator records</li>
      <li>Standalone salamander broiler installations not integrated with a range chassis (different mounting and gas line specs)</li>
      <li>Type I exhaust hood work above the range/salamander (see <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">exhaust hood repair</a>)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

